data.name: Bellsprout
data.flavorText: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

data.name: Weepinbell
data.flavorText: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

data.name: Victreebel
data.flavorText: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

data.name: Cacnea
data.flavorText: It prefers harsh environments such as deserts. It can survive for 30 days on water stored in its body.

data.name: Cacturne
data.flavorText: Packs of them follow travelers through the desert until the travelers can no longer move.

data.name: Cherubi
data.flavorText: The deeper a Cherubi's red, the more nutrients it has stockpiled in its body. And the sweeter and tastier its small ball!

data.name: Cherrim
data.flavorText: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

data.name: Carnivine
data.flavorText: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

data.name: Durant
data.flavorText: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

data.name: Scatterbug
data.flavorText: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

data.name: Spewpa
data.flavorText: The beaks of birds can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

data.name: Vivillon
data.flavorText: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

data.name: Fomantis
data.flavorText: It loves the sunshine. When it basks in the sunlight regularly, it grows up with vivid coloration.

data.name: Lurantis
data.flavorText: As it slashes into its enemies, it looks like it's dancing. Its elegant appearance has led some to call it the most glamorous Grass Pokémon.

data.name: Tapu Bulu
data.flavorText: Although it's called a guardian deity, it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

data.name: Blipbug
data.flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

data.name: Entei
data.flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

data.name: Tepig
data.flavorText: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

data.name: Pignite
data.flavorText: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

data.name: Emboar
data.flavorText: It has mastered fast and powerful fighting moves. It grows a beard of fire.

data.name: Heatmor
data.flavorText: A flame serves as its tongue, melting through the hard shell of Durant so that Heatmor can devour their insides.

data.name: Salandit
data.flavorText: This sneaky Pokémon will slink behind its prey and immobilize it with poisonous gas before the prey even realizes Salandit is there.

data.name: Salazzle
data.flavorText: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

data.name: Sizzlipede
data.flavorText: It wraps prey up with its heated body, cooking them in its coils. Once they're well-done, it will voraciously nibble them down to the last morsel.

data.name: Centiskorch
data.flavorText: While its burning body is already dangerous on its own, this excessively hostile Pokémon also has large and very sharp fangs.

data.name: Horsea
data.flavorText: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

data.name: Seadra
data.flavorText: It is capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its winglike pectoral fins and stout tail.

data.name: Kingdra
data.flavorText: It stores energy by sleeping at underwater depths at which no other life forms can survive.

data.name: Galarian Mr. Mime
data.flavorText: It can radiate chilliness from the bottoms of its feet. It'll spend the whole day tap-dancing on a frozen floor.

data.name: Galarian Mr. Rime
data.flavorText: Its amusing movements make it very popular. It releases its psychic power from the pattern on its belly.

data.name: Remoraid
data.flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

data.name: Octillery
data.flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

data.name: Corphish
data.flavorText: It was originally a Pokémon from afar that escaped to the wild. It can adapt to the dirtiest river.

data.name: Crawdaunt
data.flavorText: A brutish Pokémon that loves to battle. It will crash itself into any foe that approaches its nest.

data.name: Frillish
data.flavorText: Legend has it that the residents of a sunken ancient city changed into these Pokémon.

data.name: Jellicent
data.flavorText: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

data.name: Bruxish
data.flavorText: Its skin is thick enough to fend off Mareanie's spikes. With its robust teeth, Bruxish crunches up the spikes and eats them.

data.name: Electabuzz
data.flavorText: While it's often blamed for power outages, the truth is the cause of outages is more often an error on the part of the electric company.

data.name: Electivire
data.flavorText: A single Electivire can provide enough electricity for all the buildings in a big city for a year.

data.name: Shinx
data.flavorText: All of its fur dazzles if danger is sensed. It flees while the foe is momentarily blinded.

data.name: Luxio
data.flavorText: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

data.name: Luxray
data.flavorText: Luxray's ability to see through objects comes in handy when it's scouting for danger.

data.name: Pachirisu
data.flavorText: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

data.name: Yamper
data.flavorText: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

data.name: Boltund
data.flavorText: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

data.name: Galarian Slowpoke
data.flavorText: Because Galarian Slowpoke eat the seeds of a plant that grows only in Galar, their tails have developed a spicy flavor.

data.name: Spoink
data.flavorText: It bounces around on its tail to keep its heart pumping. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

data.name: Grumpig
data.flavorText: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

data.name: Baltoy
data.flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

data.name: Claydol
data.flavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

data.name: Chimecho
data.flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

data.name: Espurr
data.flavorText: There's enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can't be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.

data.name: Meowstic
data.flavorText: The defensive instinct of the males is strong. It's when they're protecting themselves or their partners that they unleash their full power.

data.name: Dottler
data.flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

data.name: Orbeetle
data.flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

data.name: Mankey
data.flavorText: If one gets angry, all the others around it will get angry, so silence is a rare visitor in a troop of Mankey.

data.name: Primeape
data.flavorText: The blood vessels in its brain are sturdier than those of other Pokémon, so it can stay healthy despite its constant raging.

data.name: Onix
data.flavorText: It rapidly bores through the ground at 50 mph by squirming and twisting its massive, rugged body.

data.name: Cubone
data.flavorText: It wears its mother's skull on its head, so no one knows what its bare face looks like. However, it's clear that it's always crying.

data.name: Marowak
data.flavorText: They thump their bones rhythmically to communicate among themselves. There are nearly 50 different rhythmic patterns.

data.name: Gligar
data.flavorText: It flies straight at its target's face then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

data.name: Gliscor
data.flavorText: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey… Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

data.name: Timburr
data.flavorText: Timburr that have started carrying logs that are about three times their size are nearly ready to evolve.

data.name: Gurdurr
data.flavorText: Gurdurr excels at demolition—construction is not its forte. In any case, there's skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.

data.name: Conkeldurr
data.flavorText: When going all out, this Pokémon throws aside its concrete pillars and leaps at opponents to pummel them with its fists.

data.name: Mienfoo
data.flavorText: They seclude themselves in the mountains and devote themselves to training. The form of their kicks and chops differs from pack to pack.

data.name: Mienshao
data.flavorText: When Mienshao lets out a bizarre wail, you're in danger. A flurry of kicks and chops too fast to see is about to be unleashed!

data.name: Rolycoly
data.flavorText: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

data.name: Carkol
data.flavorText: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

data.name: Coalossal
data.flavorText: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

data.name: Silicobra
data.flavorText: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

data.name: Sandaconda
data.flavorText: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

data.name: Falinks
data.flavorText: The six of them work together as one Pokémon. Teamwork is also their battle strategy, and they constantly change their formation as they fight.

data.name: Stonjourner
data.flavorText: Once a year, on a specific date and at a specific time, they gather out of nowhere and form up in a circle.

data.name: Zubat
data.flavorText: Their skin is so thin that they'll be burned if sunlight hits them. When it gets cold out, they gather together to warm one another's bodies.

data.name: Golbat
data.flavorText: They can suck down over 10 ounces of blood in one go. They have been known to drink so much blood that they can no longer fly.

data.name: Crobat
data.flavorText: It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokémon. If it can't drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.

data.name: Galarian Slowbro
data.flavorText: If this Pokémon squeezes the tongue of the Shellder biting it, the Shellder will launch a toxic liquid from the tip of its shell.

data.name: Murkrow
data.flavorText: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow's presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.

data.name: Honchkrow
data.flavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.

data.name: Houndour
data.flavorText: They make repeated eerie howls before dawn to call attention to their pack.

data.name: Houndoom
data.flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.

data.name: Morpeko
data.flavorText: Hunger hormones affect its temperament. Until its hunger is appeased, it gets up to all manner of evil deeds.

data.name: Steelix
data.flavorText: It is thought its body transformed as a result of iron accumulating internally from swallowing soil.

data.name: Mawile
data.flavorText: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

data.name: Bronzor
data.flavorText: Polishing Bronzor to a shine makes its surface reflect the truth, according to common lore. Be that as it may, Bronzor hates being polished.

data.name: Bronzong
data.flavorText: Many scientists suspect that this Pokémon originated outside the Galar region, based on the patterns on its body.

data.name: Pawniard
data.flavorText: A pack of these Pokémon forms to serve a Bisharp boss. Each Pawniard trains diligently, dreaming of one day taking the lead.

data.name: Bisharp
data.flavorText: Violent conflicts erupt between Bisharp and Fraxure over places where sharpening stones can be found.

data.name: Honedge
data.flavorText: The blue eye on the sword's handguard is the true body of Honedge. With its old cloth, it drains people's lives away.

data.name: Doublade
data.flavorText: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

data.name: Aegislash
data.flavorText: Once upon a time, a king with an Aegislash reigned over the land. His Pokémon eventually drained him of life, and his kingdom fell with him.

data.name: Aegislash
data.flavorText: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.

data.name: Spearow
data.flavorText: Due to its short wings, it can't fly long distances. It wanders about restlessly and pecks at bug Pokémon.

data.name: Fearow
data.flavorText: Carrying food through Fearow's territory is dangerous. It will snatch the food away from you in a flash!

data.name: Lickitung
data.flavorText: It licks filth clean with its tongue. Whatever it licks always stinks afterward, so whether it's really clean is…questionable.

data.name: Lickilicky
data.flavorText: It uses its tongue much more skillfully than its hands or its feet. It can deftly pick up a single small bean with its tongue.

data.name: Glameow
data.flavorText: When it's happy, Glameow demonstrates beautiful movements of its tail, like a dancing ribbon.

data.name: Purugly
data.flavorText: To make itself appear intimidatingly beefy, it tightly cinches its waist with its twin tails.

data.name: Bouffalant
data.flavorText: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

data.name: Drampa
data.flavorText: Drampa is a kind and friendly Pokémon—up until it's angered. When that happens, it stirs up a gale and flattens everything around.

data.name: Indeedee
data.flavorText: Through its horns, it can pick up on the emotions of creatures around it. Positive emotions are the source of its strength.

data.name: Octillery
data.flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

data.name: Houndoom
data.flavorText: Identifiable by its eerie howls, people a long time ago thought it was the grim reaper and feared it.
